      <scopecontent id="aspace_8d289a74c6139c36313c08e4492ecdfe">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>These papers comprise materials belonging to the Tyler and Towner families. The majority are papers of Solomon Tyler relating to the sloop <title render="italic">
               <part>Lyon</part>
            </title> (or <title render="italic">
               <part>Lion</part>
            </title>) of Branford, Connecticut, and other vessels in which he had a share. In addition to the <title render="italic">
               <part>Lyon</part>
            </title>, other ships mentioned in the collection are the sloops <title render="italic">
               <part>Polly, Annay, Success, Prosperity, Speedwell, Hopewell, Dolphin</part>
            </title>, and the schooners <title render="italic">
               <part>Unity, Success, Phenix</part>
            </title>, and <title render="italic">
               <part>Dolphin</part>
            </title>. Among the Tyler family materials are early items from the Isaac Tyler family and legal and financial documents relating to ships. Solomon Tyler recorded his general business accounts (1789-1819) in the front of his account book, and those relating to the <title render="italic">
               <part>Lyon</part>
            </title> (1789-1800) in the back.</p>
         <p>Also in the papers is a fragment of the Civil War diary, in the formed of a typed carbon, of John Edwin Towner, a descendant of Solomon Tyler.</p>
         <p>A complete photostatic copy of the papers, including the account book, has been added to the collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_e44a6dc5e198b9ecf3933b3965a1cc6a">
